261
00:17:19,528 --> 00:17:20,779
What did he say?

262
00:17:21,029 --> 00:17:25,283
He understands how sex can be
a very emotional thing for a woman.

263
00:17:25,534 --> 00:17:28,495
And he was just afraid
that I was going to get all:

264
00:17:28,745 --> 00:17:33,291
"Is he gonna call me the next day?"
and "Where is this going?"

265
00:17:33,542 --> 00:17:39,840
So he said he wanted to hold off
until he was prepared to be serious.

266
00:17:40,465 --> 00:17:45,595
So I said, "Okay. Relax, please."

267
00:17:45,846 --> 00:17:49,891
Sex can be just about two people
right there in the moment.

268
00:17:50,142 --> 00:17:53,895
If he wants to see me again, he can
call. If not, that's fine too.

269
00:17:54,146 --> 00:17:59,109
So after a lot of talking...

270
00:17:59,818 --> 00:18:03,280
...I convinced him.

271
00:18:05,490 --> 00:18:07,117
Let me get this straight.

272
00:18:07,367 --> 00:18:10,329
He got you to beg to sleep with him.

273
00:18:10,579 --> 00:18:14,750
He got you to say
he never has to call you again.

274
00:18:15,542 --> 00:18:19,630
And he got you thinking
this is a great idea?

275
00:18:22,049 --> 00:18:25,802
This man is my god!

276
00:18:32,125 --> 00:18:33,990
This one is cute. Don't you think?

277
00:18:34,193 --> 00:18:37,128
Yeah. This one's cute and
that one's cute and that one's cute.

278
00:18:37,296 --> 00:18:38,640
They're all cute, they're kittens.

279
00:18:38,700 --> 00:18:41,232
Let's just wrap one up
and get the hell out of here.

280
00:18:42,101 --> 00:18:46,837
- Are you okay?
- Yeah, me, sure.

281
00:18:50,276 --> 00:18:52,030
I know that this is
a big step for us...

282
00:18:52,100 --> 00:18:54,906
...but I've got a feeling
we're gonna be okay.

283
00:18:56,416 --> 00:18:58,714
I know, I know.

284
00:18:59,052 --> 00:19:03,512
Do you have any cats that are
really old or incredibly sick?

285
00:19:05,858 --> 00:19:08,452
Ross, I don't want one
that's about to die.

286
00:19:08,628 --> 00:19:12,564
Oh, see? We should have worked
that out before we came down here.

287
00:19:12,765 --> 00:19:13,857
Okay, sweetie.

288
00:19:14,033 --> 00:19:17,059
I'm gonna narrow it down to
this one over here...

289
00:19:17,236 --> 00:19:19,636
...and this one
with the stripes, okay?

290
00:19:19,839 --> 00:19:20,931
You pick.

291
00:19:21,240 --> 00:19:23,606
I have to pick?

292
00:19:23,776 --> 00:19:25,971
Whichever one you want.

293
00:19:28,047 --> 00:19:30,072
I don't know.

294
00:19:30,283 --> 00:19:32,410
I mean, it's not that easy to choose.

295
00:19:32,618 --> 00:19:36,816
I mean, both cats are beautiful...

296
00:19:38,925 --> 00:19:40,893
...and funny.

297
00:19:43,629 --> 00:19:47,030
You know, I'm sure I'd be
happy with either cat.

298
00:19:47,600 --> 00:19:51,001
- Do you want to take both?
- Both?

299
00:19:51,204 --> 00:19:54,640
I can't have two cats.

300
00:19:55,908 --> 00:19:59,537
Joey's the kind of guy
who could have two cats.

301
00:20:14,627 --> 00:20:17,797
I didn't get a cat.

302
00:20:18,214 --> 00:20:21,259
That's interesting.

303
00:20:21,509 --> 00:20:25,388
No, it's not "interesting."
It's very, very not interesting.

304
00:20:25,638 --> 00:20:28,599
It's actually 100%
the opposite of interesting.

305
00:20:28,849 --> 00:20:30,017
I got it, Ross.

306
00:20:30,268 --> 00:20:34,021
You had no right to say
you had feelings for me.

307
00:20:34,272 --> 00:20:36,857
I was doing great with Julie
before I knew!

308
00:20:37,108 --> 00:20:38,943
I was doing great
before I knew about you!

309
00:20:39,193 --> 00:20:41,571
You think it's easy
to see you with Julie?

310
00:20:41,821 --> 00:20:43,865
You should've said something before!

311
00:20:44,115 --> 00:20:47,368
I didn't know then.
And how come you never said anything?

312
00:20:47,618 --> 00:20:49,161
There was never a good time.

313
00:20:49,412 --> 00:20:52,915
You only had a year.
And we only hung out every night!

314
00:20:53,165 --> 00:20:54,876
Not...

315
00:20:55,126 --> 00:20:57,712
...every night.

316
00:20:57,962 --> 00:21:00,882
It's not like I didn't try.
But things got in the way.

317
00:21:01,132 --> 00:21:02,800
You know, like Italian guys...

318
00:21:03,050 --> 00:21:06,429
...or ex-fiancés...

319
00:21:06,679 --> 00:21:10,558
...or Italian guys.

320
00:21:10,766 --> 00:21:14,353
There was one Italian guy, okay?
And do you have a point?

321
00:21:14,604 --> 00:21:17,356
The point is, I don't need
this right now!

322
00:21:17,607 --> 00:21:19,275
Okay? It's too late.

323
00:21:19,525 --> 00:21:22,445
I'm with somebody else. I'm happy.
This ship has sailed!

324
00:21:22,695 --> 00:21:25,823
You're just gonna put away
your feelings for me?

325
00:21:26,073 --> 00:21:28,701
I've done it since ninth grade.
I'm good at it.

326
00:21:28,951 --> 00:21:31,370
All right, fine.
You go ahead and do that.

327
00:21:31,621 --> 00:21:32,914
I don't need your ship!

328
00:21:33,164 --> 00:21:35,541
- Good.
- Good!

329
00:21:35,750 --> 00:21:40,171
And you know what?
Now I got closure!

330
00:22:31,347 --> 00:22:34,392
Try the bottom one.

331
00:23:00,311 --> 00:23:03,773
Monica, it's 6:30 in the morning.

332
00:23:04,023 --> 00:23:06,901
We're not working out.
It's over.

333
00:23:07,151 --> 00:23:09,570
No way! With one pound to go?
Come on!

334
00:23:09,820 --> 00:23:14,533
<i>We're workin', we're movin'
We're in the zone, we're groovin'</i>

335
00:23:14,784 --> 00:23:16,619
I don't mind the last pound.

336
00:23:16,869 --> 00:23:20,623
In fact, I kind of like the last pound.

337
00:23:20,873 --> 00:23:24,001
So don't make me do anything
that I'll regret.

338
00:23:24,251 --> 00:23:27,797
What you gonna do, fat boy?

339
00:23:27,922 --> 00:23:30,549
What?

340
00:23:30,966 --> 00:23:35,596
Nothing. Except tell you it's
wonderful how much energy you have.

341
00:23:35,846 --> 00:23:37,473
Well, thanks.

342
00:23:37,723 --> 00:23:42,770
Especially considering how tough
it's been for you to find work.

343
00:23:43,896 --> 00:23:50,569
You can't tell your parents you were
fired, because they'd be disappointed.

344
00:23:53,072 --> 00:23:58,077
It's not as if you have
a boyfriend's shoulder to cry on.

345
00:23:58,577 --> 00:24:00,413
Well, no. But I...

346
00:24:00,663 --> 00:24:05,710
If it were me, I'd have difficulty
getting out of bed at all.

347
00:24:10,506 --> 00:24:13,426
You know, I try to stay positive.

348
00:24:13,676 --> 00:24:15,344
So you...

349
00:24:15,594 --> 00:24:19,557
You feel like going for a run?

350
00:24:20,808 --> 00:24:22,351
All right.

351
00:24:22,601 --> 00:24:29,233
Because you don't have to.
You could just take a nap right here.

352
00:24:31,777 --> 00:24:34,572
For a little while.
